+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019qsKCeeheToD2DKqc6CQBa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now fix Bug 5: The `handleOrderCancelled` in InventoryService checks `eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled'` but OrderService doesn't send `status` in the cancel event. The test for inventory directly sends `status: 'cancelled'`, but the OrderService cancel path doesn't. Looking more carefully: the OrderService cancel emits without `status`, and the inventory handler has a guard `if (eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled') return;`. This guard is the bug - it should not check status since the event type itself implies cancellation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":177,"cache_read_input_tokens":40886,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":177},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d98e6366-5242-4cf6-87bd-3142c9db9efe","uuid":"8b59fb74-b1e9-4a8b-b52e-45603f37a7d4"}
